$ SQL*Plus: set serveroutput
@ set serveroutput

`set serveroutput on` is necessary to see the output that was written with → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/output[`dbms_output`]

code {
set serverout[put] {on | off} [size {n | unl[imited]}] [for[mat] {wra[pped] | wor[d_wrapped] | tru[ncated]}]
code }

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath/outon[`outon.sql`] is a most simple SQL script to be put into a → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath[`$SQLPATH` directory]. It «enables»
 `dbms_output` in → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus.
